            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="792" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Adam Aivazian, subject of your despatch No. 162, is the bearer of
                            passport No. 14470, signed by Secretary of State Blaine, May 2, 1890. Is
                            it genuine and shall I demand his release?</p>
            </div>
